commit.message:
configure.ac: Always call AC_CANONICAL_HOST

This is required for host_os also with --with-cpu.

Update config.guess and config.sub files

The existing files failed to recognize loongarch64 machines. This patch pulls
the latest config.guess and config.sub files from git.savannah.gnu.org. This
brings in loongarch64 support.

Signed-off-by: Guoqi Chen <chenguoqi@loongson.cn>

Version bump to 1.0.11

* Loongarch support
* Build bugfixes
* Update configure

Signed-off-by: Nick Sanders <nick.j.sanders@gmail.com>
Include cstdint to fix compilation with GCC-13

Add LoongArch CPU support

* Add STRESSAPPTEST_CPU_LOONGARCH definition.
* Implement cpuid(), GetFeatures(), FastFlush() and GetTimestamp() or LoongArch.
* Eliminate "WARNING: Unsupported CPU ..." or similar warnings on LoongArch.
* update config.sub and config.guess for LoongArch

Signed-off-by: chenguoqi <chenguoqi@loongson.cn>

Fix x86 compilation on some systems

Some systems (or system configurations) use a compiler version
which does not have the x86 __rtdsc() intrinsic (and probably
others) defined in immintrin.h.
On those systems, compilation for x86 arch will fail. This
was reported on Debian 10, RHEL 8.x and Ubuntu 20.04.

It seems immintrin.h is mostly for x86 SIMD intrinsics, but some
compilers also put __rtdsc() there.

x86intrin.h is supposed to include immintrin.h *and* define all
the Intel processors intrinsics, so including it before immintrin.h.

configure: Check for pthread_rwlockattr_setkind_np before use

musl does not implement this therefore detect this non-posix API before
using it

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>

Replace lfs64 functions and defines

AC_SYS_LARGEFILE is already in use in configure.ac which detects
enabling lfs64 functions as needed, it will define _FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64
which should make lseek same as lseek64 since off_t is 64bit on most of
current 32bit linux platforms

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>

configure: Add --with-cpu

Some cross build systems e.g. yocto may use architectures different from cross compiler target tuple
arm-yoe-gnueabi but build for armv7a, AC_CANONICAL_HOST will fail in
this case even though target will be armv7a it will detect it as arm and
disable armv7a specific optimization paths. This option provides the
needed knob so it can be set explicitly e.g. --with-cpu=armv7a etc. if needed.

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>

stressapptest: Implement reading sysfs and use it if sysconf

sysconf params like _SC_LEVEL1_DCACHE_LINESIZE are not universally
implemented, therefore check for them being available, if not there
then read the sysfs directly to get the value

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>

Fix compile on sytems using libc++ instead of libstdc++

libc++ does not really implement __gnu_cxx namespace and it
compiles fine without this namespace, therefore detect libc++
and if it is used them exclude this namespace

See https://github.com/stressapptest/stressapptest/issues/47

Fixes

./sattypes.h:33:17: error: expected namespace name
using namespace __gnu_cxx; //NOLINT

Signed-off-by: Khem Raj <raj.khem@gmail.com>

commit.message:
add aarch64 vector copy

Add vector acceleratin for aarch64
This improves memory copy speed by a
large factor on tested devices.

TEST=Run on device, see higher BW nmbers.
TEST=force errors still finds errors.

Refactor the inverter workers

This changes the loop to a range construct which is a bit easier for both the compiler and the user to read.
Instead of stalling on every flush, mark all written cachelines with Hint, and flush them all at once after the loop.
Fix compilation on clang (and hopefully msvc)

Move the immintrin include after sattypes

whoops

In x86 targets, replace volatile asm with immintrin calls

This improves the unrolling behaviour on clang quite significantly, where previously it would ignore the `-funroll-loops` and get stuck on the asm calls.
